PER CURIAM:Â  Permanent General Assurance Corporation appeals a trial courtâ€™s grant of summary judgment to Dariell Cooper on the issue of whether Cooper may recover underinsured motorist benefits under an insurance policy not providing primary coverage on the motorcycle involved in the accident.Â  We affirm pursuant to Rule 220, SCACR and the following authority:Â  Burgess v. Nationwide Mut. Ins. Co., 361 S.C. 196, 603 S.E.2d 861 (Ct. App. 2004), cert. pending, (considering analogous facts and holding motorcyclist was entitled to underinsured motorist benefits under policy not covering motorcycle).
